<p>Across all of it, the GSD rules that matter most: <strong>weigh every meal</strong> (count treats in the daily total) and aim for steady, lean growth; <strong>feed little and often from a calm, floor-level bowl and avoid hard exercise around mealtimes</strong> to reduce bloat (GDV) risk; and <strong>watch the stools</strong> — persistently loose, greasy or pale poo, especially with a ravenous appetite and poor weight gain, warrants a vet check for EPI, which is very manageable once diagnosed. Keep exercise age-appropriate too, avoiding forced runs and repetitive jumping while the growth plates are still open.</p>

